title: GIRLS VOLLEYBALL: Penn Yan joins Wayne at top of East
text:
Larger font size Posted: Wednesday, October 21, 2015 5:00 pm GIRLS VOLLEYBALL: Penn Yan joins Wayne at top of East Times Sports Staff Finger Lakes Times | 0 comments 
NEWARK — With one night of the regular season remaining, the Finger Lakes East girls volleyball league title is still up for grabs. 
Penn Yan earned a 3-0 sweep of Newark Tuesday to pull into a tie with idle Wayne at the top of the division standings. The Mustangs (14-2, 9-2) will host Waterloo Thursday, while the Eagles (10-4, 9-2) visit Midlakes. 
Last night, Penn Yan’s Emily Wunder posted 18 digs, three blocks and two kills. Jess Decker supplied six aces, four kills and four blocks. Jess Covell chipped in six digs, three kills and three aces. 
Ladonia Smith hammered four kills for the Reds (4-7). 
Waterloo 3, Midlakes 0 
WATERLOO — The Indians’ five upperclassmen all keyed the win on Senior Night, led by Brittanie Forde’s eight digs, six kills and four aces. 
Taylor Carter checked in with four kills. Julia Benedicks registered the same number of digs. Alberta Eshenour racked up three digs. Keira O’Connor cracked a pair of kills. 
Olivia Lannon supplied four kills and a block for Midlakes (2-16, 0-11). 
Pal-Mac 3, Geneva 1 
PALMYRA — Izzy Brewer piled up 54 digs to lead Palmyra-Macedon (8-9, 5-7). Michaela Morrison put together a 33-assist, 17-dig, two-ace night. Riley Record chalked up 25 digs and nine kills. Lindsay Howell added 14 kills, six blocks and two aces. 
Erin Guinan smashed 10 kills and seven blocks for Geneva (8-5, 7-4). Shannon Gallagher collected seven blocks and a kill. Lauren Devaney pitched in with five kills and four blocks. 
FINGER LAKES WEST 
Honeoye 3, Dundee 0 
HONEOYE — Hailey Cornish celebrated Senior Night with 14 aces, 13 assists, four kills and a block for Honeoye (14-2, 8-2). Classmate Bailey Lis logged six kills, three aces and a block. 
WAYNE COUNTY 
Lyons 3, Sodus 0 
LYONS — Ayanna McDonald accumulated 19 service points in the third game to close out the win for the Lions (12-7, 9-4). McDonald finished with five aces. 
Teaonna Jenkins contributed six digs, four aces and three kills. Isis Tarver added six digs and three aces. 
Meagan Hoover clubbed four kills for the Spartans (0-17, 0-12). Sara Green served three aces. 
NR-W 3, Marion 0 
MARION — Abby Miraglia fired in nine aces and two kills for the Cougars (13-5, 11-2). Brianna Boone smacked three kills. 
Elly Hepburn notched five blocks and two kills for Marion (3-14, 3-10). 
NON-LEAGUE 
Mynderse 3, Hammondsport/Prattsburgh 1 
SENECA FALLS — Heidi Miller paced Mynderse (13-3) with nine kills, eight aces, two digs and a block. Tria Backman aided the win with 12 assists, 10 digs, three kills, a block and an ace. Kalli Kelsey came home with 10 digs, three kills, two aces and an assist.
